    "Trust in humans and automation shares similarities, supported by both empirical and neurological evidence (Lewandowsky et al., 2000; Hoff and Bashir, 2015).",
    "For instance, a three-phase experiment study by Jian et al. (2000) that included tasks of word elicitation and meaning comparison showed that the constructs of trust in humanhuman and human-automation interactions are analogous."
